//setup: node server.js
//HTTP GET: curl --silent --include 'http://localhost:3000/get/1'
//HTTP POST: curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/get?"last=obama&first=mike&phone=+123+67567+216&zip=27420&city=Oulu&address=Talentie+67"
//HTTP PATCH: curl -X PATCH http://localhost:3000/get/3?"phone=%2B465+112+212"

- HTTP server: uses Express framework
- Database: uses Sequelize framework: class Model and methods like findAll()
- No raw SQL queries
    - API:
      + allows searching information (HTTP GET)
      + allows adding information (HTTP POST)
      + allows modifying information (HTTP UPDATE)
- reponse: JSON data
- Error handling


